<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-F40042A1-1B97-4754-B3E8-AB79291ADAFB" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-F40042A1-1B97-4754-B3E8-AB79291ADAFB" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">11 The function of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">User Panel</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 11PBA05 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">LUI</compsignal></comp></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The Operator panel (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">User Panel</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 11PBA05 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">LUI</compsignal></comp>) is a monitor as well as an input device. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">It contains software that is responsible for showing a progress bar during the startup phase when the windows controller is not ready able to send the correct video to the User Panel. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When video updates are received from the Windows controller the video input from the controller is selected and shown from that moment on.
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Components:</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Operator panel is divided into several functional components: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Liquid crystal display (LCD) and touch screen, which is the main interface for the user 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Housing, which is made up of several plastic parts 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Hinge, connected to the arm on the system. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-0A6BE455-9AB1-4E27-9D49-109C9294674A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Connections</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Operator panel is connected to the system with the following connections : 
</p><fig id="GUID-336B0287-09FE-465B-9743-0C4AE70CEF7D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A233A79A-DC9C-4736-8609-FF2239560B80-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A233A79A-DC9C-4736-8609-FF2239560B80-low.png"/></fig><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> HDMI (High definition multimedia interface) video interface 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> USB interface 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Power supply 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Switch video input key 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-FC252023-6D7C-4E57-A534-377E6D7BBB91" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/></fig></section><section id="GUID-97E33635-1166-4698-AB89-FD93460CA03C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Dimensions and Weight</title><fig id="GUID-60724AC2-DDD0-438A-BD22-66C02DB862FB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-39A1F2B9-038A-48A5-B03E-C7FD4E5D57CC-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-39A1F2B9-038A-48A5-B03E-C7FD4E5D57CC-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-D45CD8D8-5413-4EE0-A9AE-67A86D8555E5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6645BC63-670F-4F9B-806A-E98FD32ADC46-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6645BC63-670F-4F9B-806A-E98FD32ADC46-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The weight of the console is 1.6kg <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="mathsymbols">± </ph>0.2kg. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Display / Touch specifications</title><p class="- topic/p ">The display specifications are : 
